## State Representation on SE(2)

```markdown
# Geometric State Representation

The robot pose evolves on the Special Euclidean Lie group:

$$
SE(2)
$$

with configuration:

$$
X =
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos\theta & -\sin\theta & x \\
\sin\theta & \cos\theta & y \\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
\in SE(2)
$$
```

---

## Lie Algebra Basis

```markdown
# Lie Algebra Basis

The Lie algebra generators are:

$$
\hat e_1 =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
\hat e_2 =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
\hat e_3 =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & -1 & 0 \\
1 & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
$$
```

---

## Lie Algebra Velocity Representation

```markdown
# Lie Algebra Velocity Representation

Any admissible body velocity is represented as:

$$
\hat\xi
=
v_x \hat e_1
+
v_y \hat e_2
+
\omega \hat e_3
\in \mathfrak{se}(2)
$$
```

---

## Exponential Mapping

```markdown
# Exponential Mapping

Robot pose evolution is computed through:

$$
X_{k+1}
=
X_k \exp(\Delta t \hat\xi)
$$
```

