---

## Continuous-Time Swimming Dynamics

```markdown
# Swimming Dynamics

$$
\dot x
=
v_y \tan(\alpha)\cos\theta
-
v_y \sin\theta
$$

$$
\dot y
=
v_y \tan(\alpha)\sin\theta
+
v_y \cos\theta
$$

$$
\dot\theta = 0
$$
```

---

## Discrete-Time Swimming Dynamics

```markdown
# Discrete-Time Swimming Dynamics

$$
x_{k+1}
=
x_k
+
\Delta t
\left(
\tan\alpha\cos\theta_k
-
\sin\theta_k
\right)
$$

$$
y_{k+1}
=
y_k
+
\Delta t
\left(
\tan\alpha\sin\theta_k
-
\cos\theta_k
\right)
$$

$$
\theta_{k+1}
=
\theta_k
$$
```

---

## Swimming Lie Algebra Representation

```markdown
# Swimming Lie Algebra Representation

$$
\hat\xi_{swim}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & v_y\tan\alpha \\
0 & 0 & v_y \\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
$$
```

---

## Swimming Exponential Mapping

```markdown
# Swimming Exponential Mapping

$$
X_{k+1}
=
X_k
\exp(\Delta t \hat\xi_{swim})
$$

which expands to:

$$
X_{k+1}
=
X_k
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & \Delta t v_y\tan\alpha \\
0 & 1 & \Delta t v_y \\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$
```

