## Continuous-Time Rolling Dynamics

```markdown
# Rolling Dynamics

$$
\dot x
=
\mu_r \omega_r
$$

$$
\dot y
=
0
$$

$$
\dot\theta
=
\omega_r
$$
```

---

## Discrete-Time Rolling Dynamics

```markdown
# Discrete-Time Rolling Dynamics

$$
x_{k+1}
=
x_k
+
\Delta t \mu_r \omega_r
$$

$$
y_{k+1}
=
y_k
$$

$$
\theta_{k+1}
=
\theta_k
+
\Delta t \omega_r
$$
```

---

## Rolling Lie Algebra Representation

```markdown
# Rolling Lie Algebra Representation

$$
\hat\xi_{roll}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & -\omega_r & \mu_r\omega_r \\
\omega_r & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
$$
```

---

## Rolling Exponential Mapping

```markdown
# Rolling Exponential Mapping

$$
X_{k+1}
=
X_k
\exp(\Delta t \hat\xi_{roll})
$$

which expands to:

$$
X_{k+1}
=
X_k
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos(\omega_r \Delta t)
&
-\sin(\omega_r \Delta t)
&
\mu_r\omega_r \\
\sin(\omega_r \Delta t)
&
\cos(\omega_r \Delta t)
&
0 \\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$
```

