# 5. Stochastic State Estimation

## Suggested File

```text
docs/theory/ekf_derivation.md
```

---

## State Evolution Model

```markdown
# State Evolution

The stochastic system evolves according to:

$$
x_{k+1}
=
A x_k
+
B u_k
+
w_k
$$

with observation model:

$$
y_k
=
C x_k
+
v_k
$$
```

---

## Prediction Step

```markdown
# EKF Prediction

$$
\hat x_{k|k-1}
=
A_k \hat x_{k-1|k-1}
+
B_k u_k
$$
```

---

## Covariance Propagation

```markdown
# Covariance Propagation

$$
P_{k|k-1}
=
A_k P_{k-1|k-1} A_k^T
+
Q_k
$$
```

---

## Standard Kalman Gain

```markdown
# Standard Kalman Gain

$$
K_k
=
P_{k|k-1} C_k^T
\left(
C_k P_{k|k-1} C_k^T
+
R_k
\right)^{-1}
$$
```

---

## State Update

```markdown
# State Update

$$
\hat x_{k|k}
=
\hat x_{k|k-1}
+
K_k
\left(
y_k
-
C_k \hat x_{k|k-1}
\right)
$$
```

---

## Correlated Noise Assumption

```markdown
# Correlated Noise Assumption

Unlike conventional EKF assumptions:

$$
\mathrm{Cov}(w_k,v_k)
\neq
0
$$
```

---

## Correlated-Noise EKF Gain

```markdown
# Correlated-Noise EKF Gain

$$
K_k
=
(P_k C_k^T + S_k)
\left(
C_k P_k C_k^T
+
R_k
+
H_k S_k
+
S_k^T H_k^T
\right)^{-1}
$$
```

---

## Correlated Covariance Update

```markdown
# Correlated Covariance Update

$$
P_{k|k}
=
(I-K_kC_k)
P_{k|k-1}
(I-K_kC_k)^T
+
K_kR_kK_k^T
-
K_kS_k^T
-
S_kK_k^T
$$
```

---

## Bayesian Filtering Interpretation

```markdown
# Bayesian Interpretation

The estimator recursively approximates:

$$
p(x_k \mid y_{1:k})
$$

through Bayesian filtering.

The recursive Bayesian update is:

$$
p(x_k|y_{1:k})
\propto
p(y_k|x_k)
p(x_k|y_{1:k-1})
$$
```

